arget%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E's%20podcast%2C%20Turley%2C%20the%20head%20of%20ChatGPT%2C%20said%20the%20single%20most%20important%20trait%20he%20looks%20for%20isn't%20technical%20prowess%2C%20but%20curiosity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20number%20one%20thing%20that%20I've%20looked%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20Turley%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it's%20actually%20my%20advice%20to%20students%20when%20they%20ask%20me%2C%20'What%20do%20I%20do%20in%20this%20world%20where%20everything's%20changing%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20so%20much%20we%20don't%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20humility%20you%20have%20to%20have%20about%20building%20on%20this%20technology.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20working%20with%20AI%20is%20less%20about%20knowing%20all%20the%20answers%20and%20more%20about%20asking%20the%20right%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20working%20with%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20asking%20the%20right%20questions%20that%20is%20the%20bottleneck%2C%20not%20necessarily%20getting%20the%20answer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Chen%2C%20OpenAI's%20chief%20research%20officer%2C%20echoed%20that%20sentiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20didn't%20have%20much%20formal%20AI%20training%20when%20he%20joined%20the%20company%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20also%20came%20into%20the%20company%20as%20a%20resident%20without%20much%20formal%20AI%20training%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BEven%20on%20research%2C%20I%20think%20increasingly%20less%2C%20we%20index%20on%20you%20have%20to%20have%20a%20Ph.D.%20in%20AI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Chen%20said%20OpenAI%20looks%20for%20candidates%20with%20%26quot%3Bagency%26quot%3B%E2%80%94the%20ability%20to%20identify%20and%20solve%20problems%20independently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20about%20being%20driven%20to%20find%2C%20'Hey%2C%20here's%20the%20problem.%20No%20one%20else%20is%20fixing%20it.%20I'm%20just%20going%20to%20go%20dive%20in%20and%20fix%20it%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20kind%20of%20self-direction%20is%20echoed%20by%20other%20OpenAI%20veterans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Deng%2C%20who%20served%20as%20OpenAI's%20VP%20of%20consumer%20product%20and%20previously%20led%20product%20teams%20at%20Meta%2C%20put%20it%20bluntly%20on%20an%20episode%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-openai-meta-exec-new-hires-success-6-months-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELenny's%20Podcast%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month%3A%20%26quot%3BIn%20six%20months%2C%20if%20I'm%20telling%20you%20what%20to%20do%2C%20I've%20hired%20the%20wrong%20person.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20expectation%20aligns%20closely%20with%20OpenAI's%20own%20culture%20of%20hands-on%20ownership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurley%20recalled%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-launch-growing-pains-chaos-employees-firings-poor-management-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20itself%20was%20born%20out%20of%20a%20hackathon-style%20sprint%2C%20with%20people%20from%20across%20teams%20%E2%80%94%20including%20infrastructure%20and%20supercomputing%20%E2%80%94%20coming%20together%20to%20ship%20a%20product%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFundamentally%2C%26quot%3B%20Turley%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20just%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20with%20agency%20who%20can%20ship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20this%20is%20what%20makes%20OpenAI%20unique%20and%20is%20a%20key%20focus%20of%20the%20company's%20hiring%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwant-work-at-openai-curiosity-grit-matter-more-than-phd-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751449985000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6864f67af748d8c055f4ca69%3