%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouple-in-tech-budget-300k-income-together-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efinancial%20plan%20highly%20adaptable%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20that%20it%20was%20easy%20to%20shift%20once%20we%20realized%20we%20wanted%20to%20grow%20our%20family.%20These%205%20steps%20were%20critical%20to%20our%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222ae5a5e5-fa54-486e-b23a-8363548ae103%5C%22%3E1.%20We%20made%20a%20habit%20of%20saving%20more%20than%20we%20%26quot%3Bhad%20to%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bshould%26quot%3B%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20spent%20a%20decade%20saving%20between%2030%20to%2040%20percent%20of%20our%20income%20because%20we%20prioritized%20future%20flexibility.%20We%20also%20knew%20how%20powerful%20%26quot%3Bfrontloading%26quot%3B%20our%20savings%20could%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20reap%20the%20biggest%20benefits%20from%20the%20power%20of%20compounding%20returns%20on%20investments%2C%20you%20need%20to%20stay%20invested%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time%20period.%20And%20the%20earlier%20you%20start%2C%20the%20more%20you%20can%20benefit%20from%20the%20compounding%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Eric%20Roberge%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686485253d5881a51c1c7fc4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEric%20Roberge%20is%20a%20financial%20advisor.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Eric%20Roberge%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20save%20less%20now%2C%20partly%20because%20we%20have%20all%20kinds%20of%20expenses%20we%20did%20not%20have%20before%20adding%20a%20child%20to%20the%20family%20%E2%80%94%20school%20tuition%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffree-lap-child-vs-pay-seat-plane-safer-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethird%20airplane%20seat%20on%20trips%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20endless%20stuffed%20animal%20acquisition%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%26quot%3Bsaving%20less%26quot%3B%20does%20not%20mean%20abandoning%20the%20savings%20habit%20altogether.%20We%20now%20save%20about%2025%25%20of%20our%20income%20annually.%20While%20it's%20less%20than%20before%2C%20it's%20still%20higher%20than%20average%2C%20though%20it%20feels%20like%20an%20easy%20target%20to%20meet%20after%20sustaining%20higher%20savings%20rates%20for%20so%20long.%20It's%20also%20sufficient%20to%20meet%20our%20biggest%20current%20financial%20goal%20of%20retiring%20in%20our%2050s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2294c72ce5-86d5-4910-a76a-a7fd54e3303b%5C%22%3E2.%20We%20avoided%20major%20fixed%20costs%20or%20hard-to-reverse%20decisions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20we%20were%20child-free%20we%20opted%20out%20of%20the%20biggest%20fixed%20cost%20most%20people%20put%20into%20their%20budgets%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhow-to-buy-a-house-step-by-step-guide%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebuying%20a%20house%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20definitive%20clarity%20on%20what%20the%20future%20might%20look%20like%2C%20we%20prioritized%20the%20flexibility%20and%20ease%20of%20renting%20even%20when%20everyone%20around%20us%20was%20buying%20homes.%20We%20reasoned%20that%20we%20should%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20fact%20we%20had%20no%20external%20force%20tying%20us%20to%20a%20specific%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomebuying%20is%20a%20specific%20example%2C%20but%20we%20tried%20to%20use%20this%20frame%20of%20thinking%20more%20generally%20to%20help%20us%20avoid%20very%20large%20fixed%20costs%20or%20decisions%20that%20were%20hard%20to%20undo.%20If%20a%20choice%20in%20the%20moment%20would%20narrow%20our%20options%20for%20tomorrow%2C%20we%20tended%20to%20view%20it%20as%20a%20sub-optimal%20choice%20and%20sought%20other%20alternatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2291ed2cc8-75c6-4507-89e7-07a7e33ea52b%5C%22%3E3.%20We%20kept%20lifestyle%20inflation%20to%20a%20minimum%20along%20the%20way%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20our%20income%20grew%2C%20we%20rarely%20increased%20our%20spending.%20This%20allowed%20us%20to%20create%20a%20larger%20and%20larger%20gap%20between%20what%20we%20earned%20and%20what%20we%20spent%20%E2%80%94%20giving%20us%20a%20surplus%20we%20could%20save%20and%20invest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20adding%20a%20new%20recurring%20expense%2C%20we%20asked%20ourselves%20if%20it%20aligned%20with%20our%20values%20or%20provided%20benefits%20like%20giving%20us%20the%20ability%20to%20buy%20back%20our%20time.%20If%20not%2C%20we%20didn't%20allow%20that%20line%20item%20to%20add%20to%20our%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20did%20eventually%20buy%20a%20house%2C%20we%20looked%20at%20homes%20that%20were%20significantly%20less%20expensive%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbeyondyourhammock.com%2Ffinancial-advisor-for-buying-a-home%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhat%20a%20lender%20would%20call%20affordable%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20ensure%20we%20didn't%20max%20out%20our%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229ab619fc-d185-42f4-8217-5ef3f9a8f0cf%5C%22%3E4.%20We%20said%20no%20to%20traditional%20FIRE-style%20retirement%20goals%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20trying%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20workforce%20on%20the%20slimmest%20investment%20portfolio%20possible%2C%20as%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Ffinancial-independence-retire-early%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFIRE%20strategies%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20were%20extremely%20popular%20in%20the%202010s%20aimed%20to%20do%2C%20we%20worked%20to%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3Ecreate%20work%20we%20loved%20and%20didn't%20want%20to%20run%20away%20from%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3Eprioritize%20sustainable%20income%20growth%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpinching-pennies-early-retirement-better-idea-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%20efforts%20to%20live%20as%20frugally%20as%20possible%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDoing%20so%20allowed%20us%20to%20harness%20our%20increasing%20cash%20flow%20power%20for%20present-day%20purchases%20and%20more%20contributions%20to%20growth%20assets%20in%20our%20investment%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dd0e5f78-2582-4e59-b2b0-d25457c83c09%5C%22%3E5.%20We%20pivoted%20when%20the%20situation%20called%20for%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20works%20today%20might%20not%20work%20in%20the%20future%20if%20things%20change%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that's%20okay.%20Being%20willing%20to%20change%20is%20a%20huge%20asset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20had%20our%20daughter%20in%202021%2C%20we%20chose%20to%20save%20a%20little%20less%20so%20that%20we%20could%20spend%20a%20little%20more%20on%20her%20as%20well%20as%20things%20as%20a%20family.%20We%20did%20this%20knowing%20that%20a%20higher%20level%20of%20spending%20introduced%20a%20bit%20more%20long-term%20risk%20into%20our%20plan%2C%20due%20to%20taking%20our%20foot%20off%20the%20gas%20in%20terms%20of%20contributions%20to%20long-term%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20the%20only%20constant%20is%20change%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20from%20external%20forces%20you%20can't%20control%20or%20from%20the%20choices%20you%20willingly%20make%20with%20full%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20willing%20you%20are%20to%20adapt%20to%20the%20situation%20at%20hand%2C%20the%20more%20likely%20you'll%20be%20to%20continue%20on%20a%20track%20for%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20being%20proactive%2C%20accounting%20for%20unpredictability%2C%20and%20having%20contingency%20plans%20in%20place%2C%20you'll%20better%20position%20yourself%20(and%20your%20money)%20for%20whatever%20life%20throws%20at%20you%20%E2%80%94%20without%20having%20to%20give%20up%20long-term%20goals%20you're%20working%20hard%20to%20achieve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinancial-planner-steps-retirement-before-deciding-kids-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Inside