-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboyfriends%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20girlfriends%2C%20and%20even%2C%20in%20rare%20cases%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-who-married-ai-chatbot-open-to-real-world-dating-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espouses%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20see%20this%20as%20dystopian%3B%20others%20see%20it%20as%20a%20band-aid%20for%20the%20so-called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmodern-loneliness%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloneliness%20epidemic%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20and%20to%20others%2C%20it's%20a%20godsend.%20But%20as%20developing%20relationships%20with%20chatbots%20becomes%20more%20normalized%2C%20what%20remains%20more%20stigmatized%2C%20perhaps%2C%20is%20when%20people%20use%20generative%20AI%20to%20foster%20their%20human%20relationships%2C%20in%20texts%20to%20their%20IRL%20friends%2C%20partners%2C%20and%20families.%20Research%20shows%20that%20people%20think%20of%20people%20more%20negatively%20when%20they%20receive%20a%20text%20that%20appears%20AI-generated%2C%20and%20social%20media%20is%20abound%20with%20ChatGPT%20police.%20There%20are%20telltale%20signs%2C%20like%20em%20dashes%20or%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Bdelve%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-cant-identify-ai-generated-text-bad-for-internet-models-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20favors%20and%20has%20injected%20into%20the%20speech%20of%20its%20super%20users%2C%20the%20sleuths%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBringing%20GenAI%20into%20our%20personal%20conversation%20could%20transform%20how%20we%20perceive%20one%20another%20and%20how%20we%20socialize.%20We've%20long%20grown%20comfortable%20with%20autocorrect%20and%20predictive%20text%20helping%20us%20spit%20out%20emails%20and%20texts.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-openai-ai-dictionary-help-understand-nvidia-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elarge%20language%20models%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20entirely%20outsource%20the%20labor%20of%20comforting%20and%20confronting%20our%20friends.%20New%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.media.mit.edu%2Fpublications%2Fyour-brain-on-chatgpt%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20from%20MIT%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20that%20people%20using%20ChatGPT%20to%20assist%20with%20writing%20essays%20may%20get%20lazier%20and%20increasingly%20dependent%20on%20the%20technology%20with%20time%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bconsistently%20underperformed%20at%20neural%2C%20linguistic%2C%20and%20behavioral%20levels%26quot%3B%20compared%20to%20control%20groups%20that%20either%20used%20Google%20or%20no%20aid%20to%20write%20their%20essays.%20As%20we%20start%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-use-chatgpt-for-dating-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGenAI%20to%20flirt%20on%20dating%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20write%20wedding%20vows%2C%20or%20confront%20friends%20and%20family%20in%20tough%20conversations%2C%20will%20it%20similarly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-brainstorming-addiction-dependence-negative-consequences-mit-research-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeteriorate%3C%2Fa%3E%20our%20social%20muscles%20and%20ability%20to%20connect%20to%20one%20another%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDevelopment%20and%20adoption%20of%20AI%20is%20far%20outpacing%20the%20study%20of%20its%20social%20impacts%2C%20says%20Jess%20Hohenstein%2C%20a%20former%20AI%20researcher%20at%20Cornell%20University.%20But%20there%20is%20concern%20that%20the%20tech%20might%20undermine%20trust%20in%20how%20we%20text%20each%20other.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20know%20who%20we're%20actually%20talking%20to%2C%20and%20I%20want%20to%20talk%20to%20my%20friends%20and%20have%20validation%20that%20it's%20actually%20them%20that's%20talking%20to%20me%20and%20giving%20me%20feedback%20and%20listening%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Hohenstein%20says.%20%26quot%3BCould%20we%20potentially%20be%20moving%20to%20a%20place%20where%20face-to-face%20interactions%20are%20the%20only%20interactions%20we%20can%20truly%20trust%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20AI%20will%20affect%20our%20convos%20depends%20on%20how%20the%20tech%20is%20chiming%20in.%20For%20each%20offended%20recipient%20of%20a%20text%20that%20reads%20like%20it%20was%20copied%20and%20pasted%20straight%20from%20ChatGPT%20instead%20of%20from%20your%20bestie's%20heart%2C%20there%20are%20people%20who%20feel%20AI%20helps%20put%20your%20best%2C%20most%20polished%20self%20forward.%20The%20issue%2C%20experts%20tell%20me%2C%20depends%20on%20how%20authentic%20to%20you%20the%20sentiment%20remains.%20If%20you're%20fully%20presenting%20%26quot%3BAI%20in%20conversation%20as%20yourself%2C%20then%20you're%20not%20being%20authentic%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Marisa%20T.%20Cohen%2C%20who%20is%20dating%20app%20Hily's%20%26quot%3Bauthentic%20relationship%20expert.%26quot%3B%20But%20if%20you're%20asking%20AI%20to%20coach%20you%20to%20be%20wittier%20or%20kinder%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat's%20just%20maybe%20giving%20you%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20assistance%26quot%3B%20akin%20to%20asking%20friends%20or%20self-help%20articles%20for%20a%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202023%20study%20out%20of%20The%20Ohio%20State%20University%20underscores%20the%20potential%20complications%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-text-friends-dont-use-study-finds-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etexting%20friends%20with%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Participants%20were%20told%20they%20had%20a%20years-long%20friendship%20with%20a%20fictional%20Taylor%2C%20and%20told%20to%20text%20her%20seeking%20support%2C%20advice%2C%20or%20to%20tell%20her%20their%20birthday%20was%20coming%20up.%20They%20then%20received%20replies%20and%20were%20told%20that%20they%20either%20came%20directly%20from%20Taylor%2C%20that%20Taylor%20had%20human%20help%20writing%20the%20message%2C%20or%20that%20Taylor%20used%20gen%20AI%20to%20craft%20the%20response.%20Both%20AI%20and%20human%20intervention%20led%20people%20to%20feel%20that%20their%20relationship%20with%20Taylor%20was%20not%20very%20close%2C%20and%20the%20AI%20messages%20were%20also%20rated%20as%20less%20appropriate%20responses.%20Similarly%2C%20a%202023%20study%20from%20Cornell%20University%20found%20that%20conversations%20become%20more%20efficient%20and%20people%20use%20more%20positive%20language%20when%20conversing%20with%20the%20help%20of%20AI%20smart%20replies%2C%20but%20people%20also%20had%20more%20negative%20evaluations%20of%20others%20more%20who%20used%20algorithmic%20responses%20(or%20those%20they%20think%20might%20be%20using%20AI).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20really%20just%20see%20this%20critical%20disconnect%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Hohenstein%2C%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20research%20from%20Cornell.%20%26quot%3BUsing%20AI%20to%20communicate%20actually%20can%20kind%20of%20improve%20the%20way%20that%20we%20talk%20to%20each%20other%2C%20but%20there's%20this%20perception%20where%20it's%20judged%20so%20negatively%2C%20and%20we%20think%20this%20could%20be%20due%20to%20these%20societal%20assumptions%20about%20AI%20kind%20of%20lacking%20authenticity%20and%20being%20less%20human.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20is%20flush%20with%20posts%20from%20people%20hurt%20to%20learn%20their%20loved%20ones%20are%20talking%20to%20them%20with%20AI.%20One%20person%20complained%20that%20receiving%20a%20clearly%20AI-generated%20text%20made%20it%20seem%20%26quot%3Blike%20our%20friendship%20is%20a%20chore.%26quot%3B%20Another%20says%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20YOUR%20letter%20to%20me%2C%20so%20if%20I%20find%20out%20an%20AI%20(or%20friend)%20wrote%20it%20for%20you%2C%20that%20certainly%20won't%20make%20me%20think%20highly%20of%20you.%26quot%3B%20According%20to%20a%20new%20survey%20from%20Hily%2C%2045%25%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20say%20using%20AI%20in%20dating%20makes%20the%20process%20less%20authentic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20awkwardness%20of%20using%20AI%20as%20a%20mediator%20in%20a%20conversation%20may%20stem%20from%20the%20very%20nature%20of%20how%20large%20language%20models%20work%2C%20which%20is%20based%20on%20prediction%20and%20probability.%20%26quot%3BTelling%20you%20what%20is%20the%20most%20likely%20next%20best%20word%20is%20just%20so%20different%20from%20telling%20you%20what%20I%20think%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Quinn%20White%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20philosophy%20at%20Harvard%20University.%20When%20AI%20becomes%20a%20mediator%20in%20the%20conversation%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20fundamentally%20different%20from%20what%20we're%20doing%20when%20we%20talk%20with%20each%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20White%20says.%20People%20come%20to%20friends%20when%20they%20want%20to%20be%20heard%2C%20and%20ultimately%20to%20receive%20an%20opinion%20from%20that%20friend%2C%20not%20from%20a%20bot%20trained%20on%20all%20of%20the%20available%20information%20on%20the%20internet.%20And%20a%20good%20friend%20will%20listen%2C%20validate%20you%2C%20and%20tell%20you%20what%20you%20need%20to%20hear%2C%20not%20just%20what%20you%20statistically%20may%20want%20to%20hear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChiappetta%20says%20she%20called%20her%20friend%20out%2C%20nicely%2C%20asking%20if%20the%20text%20was%20generated%20by%20AI.%20Her%20friend%20copped%20to%20using%20ChatGPT%20for%20parts%20of%20her%20response%2C%20but%20not%20all%2C%20and%20Chiappetta%20dropped%20the%20inquisition%20from%20there.%20She%20says%20she%20has%20since%20noticed%20some%20other%20longer%20texts%20from%20the%20friend%20that%20also%20have%20hints%20of%20AI%20in%20them.%20But%20that%20doesn't%20make%20Chiappetta%20less%20likely%20to%20turn%20to%20the%20friend%20for%20advice%20or%20value%20her%20less.%20%26quot%3BShe's%20still%20a%20really%20good%20friend%2C%26quot%3B%20Chiappetta%20says%2C%20and%20is%20comforted%20by%20the%20thought%20that%20she%20is%20still%20getting%20through%20to%20her%20friend%2C%20even%20if%20there's%20an%20AI%20mediator%20creeping%20in%20the%20chat.%20%26quot%3BGenerally%2C%20I%20like%20ChatGPT's%20advice.%20It's%20still%20helpful%20to%20get%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20who%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Ffor-some-autistic-people-chatgpt-is-a-lifeline%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eneurodivergent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20contending%20with%20social%20anxiety%2C%20or%20facing%20a%20tough%20conversation%2C%20GenAI%20tools%20can%20make%20for%20helpful%20dress%20rehearsal%20for%20conversations%20with%20friends.%20%26quot%3BIncorporating%20generative%20AI%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20caring%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20other%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20David%20Deal%2C%20a%20marketing%20consultant%2C%20tells%20me.%20The%2062-year-old%20has%20used%20ChatGPT%20recently%20to%20work%20through%20conversations%20with%20much%20younger%20people%3B%20one%20a%20mentee%2C%20and%20one%20a%20relative.%20Deal%20has%20used%20ChatGPT%20to%20workshop%20a%20response%20to%20his%20mentee%2C%20telling%20the%20bot%20he%20didn't%20want%20to%20come%20off%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bmansplaining%20jerk%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20asking%20for%20help%20crafting%20an%20affirming%20reply%20to%20a%20young%20woman%20%E2%80%94%20the%20large%20language%20models%2C%20he%20says%2C%20have%20evolved%20to%20understand%20context%20like%20that%2C%20which%20was%20top%20of%20mind%20in%20his%20response.%20The%20chatbot%2C%20Deal%20says%2C%20suggested%20he%20lead%20the%20response%20with%20more%20outright%20empathy%20and%20restate%20how%20she%20was%20feeling%20to%20show%20he%20had%20been%20actively%20listening%20to%20her%20concerns.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20that%20I%20would%20have%20done%20that%20in%20my%20first%20reply%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20times%20when%20we%20may%20be%20better%20off%20showing%20up%20as%20a%20muted%2C%20less%20authentic%20version%20of%20ourselves.%20That's%20the%20version%20of%20herself%20Sarah%2C%20who%20asked%20me%20not%20to%20use%20her%20last%20name%20because%20she's%20still%20in%20the%20process%20of%20finalizing%20a%20divorce%2C%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20be%20as%20she%20works%20through%20a%20custody%20agreement%20and%20the%20splitting%20up%20of%20assets%20with%20her%20soon-to-be%20ex-husband.%20She's%20relying%20on%20ChatGPT%20to%20translate%20acrimonious%20texts%20to%20him.%20%26quot%3BWhenever%20you're%20in%20anything%20that's%20contentious%2C%20or%20you're%20worried%20about%20anybody%20reading%20your%20texts%2C%20you%20just%20want%20to%20be%20really%20polite%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20moments%20when%20I%2C%20as%20myself%2C%20cannot%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20will%20type%20up%20what%20she%20wants%20to%20say%2C%20with%20all%20the%20emotionally-charged%20snark%20and%20frustration%20over%20coordinating%20coparenting%2C%20and%20ask%20ChatGPT%20to%20rephrase%20the%20ask%20as%20%26quot%3Brespectful%2C%20but%20with%20firm%20boundaries%26quot%3B%20to%20get%20across%20the%20logistical%20info%20she%20needs%20to%20say.%20Sarah%20gets%20the%20satisfaction%20of%20still%20putting%20her%20rage%20into%20words%2C%20but%20also%20the%20feeling%20of%20%26quot%3Bmoral%20superiority%26quot%3B%20as%20she%20sends%20texts%20to%20her%20ex%20that%20are%20calm%2C%20cool%2C%20and%20collected%2C%20and%20he%20responds%20with%20cheap%20jabs%2C%20sometimes%20made%20even%20angrier%20by%20her%20composure.%20%26quot%3BIt%20does%20a%20good%20job%20of%20separating%20yourself%20from%20a%20hostile%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20in%20a%20very%20active%20group%20chat%2C%20where%20six%20of%20us%20jump%20between%20topics%20every%20day.%20If%20the%20chat%20really%20takes%20off%20and%20you're%20the%20only%20one%20on%20do%20not%20disturb%2C%20it's%20common%20to%20pick%20up%20your%20phone%20to%20hundreds%20of%20unread%20messages.%20I%20wondered%20if%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-making-us-weird-artificial-intelligence-disrupting-work-social-life-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20step%20in%20and%20summarize%20when%20this%20happens%2C%20so%20I%20fed%20it%20a%20few%20days%20of%20group%20chat%20content.%20The%20chatbot%20was%20accurate%2C%20but%20missed%20the%20mark%20on%20the%20kind%20of%20humor%20only%20humans%2C%20and%20sometimes%20close%20friends%2C%20can%20get.%20One%20friend%20jokingly%20wished%20us%20all%20a%20happy%20%26quot%3BHoagie%20Day%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20ChatGPT%20summarized%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bculturally%20significant%26quot%3B%20celebration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bot%20did%20a%20decent%20job%20of%20summarizing%20a%20section%20where%20we%20all%20went%20back%20and%20forth%20trying%20to%20work%20out%20details%20for%20a%20camping%20trip.%20I%20asked%20then%20what%20I%20should%20say%20next%2C%20ChatGPT%20suggested%20something%20on%20topic%20and%20something%20%26quot%3Bhumorous%26quot%3B%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20only%20coming%20camping%20if%20someone%20promises%20to%20take%20a%20dramatic%20candid%20of%20me%20staring%20into%20the%20woods%20like%20I'm%20in%20a%20folk%20album%20cover%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20which%2C%20if%20I%20ever%20sent%20this%2C%20I'm%20trusting%20my%20friends%20would%20call%20a%20wellness%20check%20on%20me%20to%20make%20sure%20I%20haven't%20been%20kidnapped.%20For%20a%20TL%3BDR%20on%20what%20your%20friends%20are%20saying%2C%20chatbots%20might%20help%20in%20a%20pinch.%20But%20if%20you%20want%20your%20friends%20to%20maintain%20their%20respect%20for%20you%2C%20it's%20still%20best%20to%20type%20with%20your%20own%20two%20thumbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cd